 Cowboys compete at the Houston Livestock Show in Houston, Texas, the United States, March 4, 2022. The Houston Livestock Show and Rodeo, with a history of 90 years, is full of cowboy culture and customs of the American West. The festival kicks off on Feb. 28 this year and will conclude on March 20. (Xinhua/Xu Jianmei)  Horses run at the Houston Livestock Show in Houston, Texas, the United States, March 2, 2022. The Houston Livestock Show and Rodeo, with a history of 90 years, is full of cowboy culture and customs of the American West. The festival kicks off on Feb. 28 this year and will conclude on March 20. (Xinhua/Xu Jianmei)  A woman takes a selfie during the Houston Livestock Show in Houston, Texas, the United States, March 4, 2022. The Houston Livestock Show and Rodeo, with a history of 90 years, is full of cowboy culture and customs of the American West. The festival kicks off on Feb. 28 this year and will conclude on March 20. (Xinhua/Xu Jianmei)